  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Private Chef",
  "description": "<p>A distinguished private household is seeking an exceptional Private Chef with refined culinary expertise and impeccable service standards. The successful candidate will curate elevated dining experiences tailored to the family’s lifestyle, preferences, and wellness needs.<br /><br />                                                                          <u><strong>PRIVATE CHEF</strong></u></p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Serve exclusively in a private household, providing personalised culinary serviceS for their daily meals</p></li><li><p>Plan customised menus tailored to the employer’s dietary needs, health goals, and taste preferences.</p></li><li><p>Source and purchase high-quality fresh ingredients; manage kitchen inventory and prepare daily meals.</p></li><li><p>Plan, coordinate, and execute meal preparations for household events such as dinner parties, celebrations, holidays, and other functions.</p></li><li><p>Oversee all kitchen operations, ensuring the highest standards of food safety, cleanliness, and hygiene.</p></li><li><p>Create and refine new recipes as appropriate to keep menus fresh, diverse, and enjoyable.</p></li><li><p>Maintain flexibility in responding to changing schedules; role includes travelling overseas with the employer when required.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><p>Minimum 10 years of proven culinary experience in premium restaurants or hotels, with strong mastery of both International and Asian cuisines.</p></li><li><p>Extensive knowledge of diverse culinary techniques, ingredients, and cooking methods.</p></li><li><p>Strong organisational and time management skills, ensuring timely preparation and service of all meals.</p></li><li><p>Excellent interpersonal and communication skills to understand the employer’s preferences, anticipate needs, and handle feedback professionally.</p></li><li><p>Travel internationally with the family and adapt seamlessly to various environments</p></li></ul>",
